064e\u0631\u0650\u0628\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2696,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/31\/quran-sunnah-then-ijtihad\/","url_meta":{"origin":35084,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ijtihad: Judge with the Quran, Sunnah, then your opinion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 31, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Harith ibn 'Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, sent Mu\u2019adh to Yemen and he said, \u201cHow will you judge?\u201d Mu\u2019adh said, \u201cI will judge according to the Book of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cWhat if it is not in the Book of Allah?\u201d Mu\u2019adh\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33794,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/20\/prophet-left-us-everything\/","url_meta":{"origin":35084,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Prophecy: The Prophet left us everything we need to know","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, left us behind and no bird flaps with its wings but that he had given us some knowledge about it. Abu Hatim said, \u201cIt means by his commands, his prohibitions, his stories, his actions, and his permissions,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32431,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/22\/hold-fast-to-ayat-of-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":35084,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Hold fast to the verses of Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 22, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Awf ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cObey me as long as I am here with you. You must hold firmly to the verses of Allah. Permit what they permit and forbid what they forbid.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r 18\/38 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/04\/ahmad-sunnah-tafseer-quran\/","url_meta":{"origin":35084,"position":5},"title":"Ahmad on Tafsir: The Sunnah is exegesis, explanation of Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Fadl ibn Ziyad reported: I heard Ahmad Ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, respond to a question on the opinion that the Sunnah overrules the Quran. Ahmad said, \u201cI do not dare say that. Rather, the Sunnah is the explanation of the Book and its clarification.\u201d Source: al-Bah\u0323r\u2026","rel":"","cont